         <abstract>
            <p>The business of water is a hot topic. Representatives from a local civic group and Colorado State University recently held a briefing in Fort Collins, Colo., on ways to manage the Poudre River. More than 300 people attended. Earlier this year, I attended a meeting at Tampa Bay (Fla.) Water, at which there was a high level of citizen interest in water quality, rates, and the environment, as well as managing nonpotable water systems. People are passionate about water—potable and nonpotable.</p>
